{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Divider"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixes this view at its ideal size."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/divider\/fixedsize()"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","title":"fixedSize()","platforms":[{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"10.15","name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"13.0","name":"tvOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"1.0","name":"visionOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false},{"introducedAt":"6.0","name":"watchOS","unavailable":false,"deprecated":false,"beta":false}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE9fixedSizeQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore7DividerV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fixedSize"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","remoteSource":{"fileName":"FixedSizeLayout.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Layout\/FixedSizeLayout.swift#L144"}},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fixedSize"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Return Value","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A view that fixes this view at its ideal size.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During the layout of the view hierarchy, each view proposes a size to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"each child view it contains. If the child view doesn’t need a fixed size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"it can accept and conform to the size offered by the parent."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" view placed in an explicitly sized frame wraps","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and truncates its string to remain within its parent’s bounds:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixedSize()"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier can be used to create a view that maintains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ideal size","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of its children both dimensions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["Text(\"A single line of text, too long to fit in a box.\")","    .fixedSize()","    .frame(width: 200, height: 200)","    .border(Color.gray)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can result in the view exceeding the parent’s bounds, which may or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"may not be the effect you want."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can think of "},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the creation of a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"counter proposal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the view size proposed to a view by its parent. The ideal size of a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"view, and the specific effects of "},{"code":"fixedSize()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" depends on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"particular view and how you have configured it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a view that fixes the view’s size in either the horizontal or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertical dimensions, see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View\/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Divider\/fixedSize()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View/fixedSize(horizontal:vertical:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fixedSize"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"horizontal"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"vertical"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentif